      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 127: `bodyOverwrite` from plugin data is accepted as the displayed message body without any validation or provenance checks. This lets plugin-provided metadata fully replace user-visible chat content, which can spoof what was actually sent and may interact badly with downstream body parsing/rendering. Consider using a namespaced key and only applying it for trusted/expected plugin handlers, while preserving the original body for clear UI affordances.\n```suggestion\nconst auto bodyOverwriteIt \u003d msg.pluginData.constFind(\"jami.bodyOverwrite\");\nif (bodyOverwriteIt !\u003d msg.pluginData.constEnd() \u0026\u0026 isTrustedPluginOverwrite(msg.pluginData))\n    body \u003d *bodyOverwriteIt;\n```",
